sentences: Gaetano "James" Senese (born 6 January 1945) is an Italian saxophonist, composer, and singer-songwriter.
He made his professional debut in the 1960s, as a member of the rhythm and blues band The Showmen (later known as Showmen 2), with whom he won the 1968 edition of Cantagiro.

In 1974 Senese co-founded and led the critically acclaimed jazz-rock group Napoli Centrale.
After the group disbanded in 1978, he started a long collaboration with Pino Daniele, both in studio and on stage.
His first solo album was released in 1983 by Polydor Records.
